   received widespread attention for their expertise in estimating causal
   effects within high-dimensional complex data. However, the DML model is
   sensitive to the presence of outliers and heavy-tailed noise in the
   outcome variable. In this paper, we propose the robust double machine
   learning (RDML) model to achieve a robust estimation of causal effects
   when the distribution of the outcome is contaminated by outliers or
   exhibits symmetrically heavy-tailed characteristics.ResultsIn the
